{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "From the final voxel feature V fin, we apply a 3D deconvolution to obtain the upsampled feature V up ∈ R C×X×Y ×Z, which is then decoded by a lightweight MLP to produce per-voxel semantics.",
    "The same decoding procedure is applied in the RefineNet forecasting head using V refwarp, as well as in the occupied head, which takes M s to determine whether each voxel in the X × Y × Z space is occupied or empty.",
    "Additionally, to further enhance semantic representation learning, we apply an auxiliary mask decoder built upon V fin, following Co-DETR [50]; this module adopts multiple Mask2Formerbased [5] heads to predict per-class occupancy masks.",
    "Loss FunctionsTo optimize our model, we combine multiple task-specific loss functions.",
    "For depth estimation, we adopt the depth loss L depth from BEVDepth [21]."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Additionally, to further enhance semantic representation learning, we apply an auxiliary mask decoder built upon V fin, following Co-DETR [50]; this module adopts multiple Mask2Formerbased [5] heads to predict per-class occupancy masks.",
    "For depth estimation, we adopt the depth loss L depth from BEVDepth [21]."
